Adult male.description: Lucy's Warblers may be confused with juvenile Verdins, but the base of the bill is thinner on Lucy's than Verdin. Lucy's also have a faint eyering that juvenile Verdins lack.

Male (Interior).description: Bushtits may be confused with juvenile Verdins, but they have a smaller bill and a longer tail.

Female/nonbreeding male.description: Compared to juvenile Verdins, Blue-gray Gnatcatchers have a white eyering and dark tail; 2 features that juvenile Verdins lack.
